article.headline: Brown 100, Dartmouth 76
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Adrian Williams scored 26 points and Peter Sullivan had a double-double to lead Brown to a 100-76 rout over struggling Dartmouth on Saturday. Sullivan finished with 17 points and 11 rebounds for the Bears (11-15, 4-8 Ivy League), who made 13 3-pointers and went 29 of 34 from the free throw line. Sean McGonagill scored 14 points, Tucker Halpern had 12 and Garrett Leffelman added 11. From the start, Brown did not have trouble with the Big Green (5-21, 1-11), who have lost nine straight games. The Bears led by as many as 26 points in the first half on Williams' 3-pointer and eventually went into halftime with a 51-30 lead. Dartmouth cut the Bears' lead to 16 points in the second half, but never posed a threat. R.J. Griffin led the Big Green with 19 points, Clive Weeden had 11 points and 12 rebounds, and Jabari Trotter added 12 points.
